{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489591","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489591"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:22:47+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:22:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"698"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"698","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/698"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.56,0.22,0.04,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"698"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"32443"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"698","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/698"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"698"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18018"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"20"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"846"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7831"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8029"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42129"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"32443","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/32443"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring a routine assessment, his general practitioner notices a lesion on this 87-year-old man\u0027s left upper eyelid (image). She is told that this has been present for many years and does not bother him. It is painless but has now started to itch. It has had no significant change in appearance over the years. He has several similar lesions on his back. His medical history includes hypertension for which he takes captopril. He has a 20-pack-year smoking history.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Melanoma","Seborrhoeic keratosis","Melanocytic nevus","Lentigo","Pigmented basal cell carcinoma"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ETogether with the longevity of the history, the waxy and warty brownish-black, well-demarcated appearance of the lesion is consistent with a \u003Cstrong\u003Eseborrhoeic keratosis. \u003C/strong\u003EThey typically have an appearance of being stuck on the skin surface and their colour can vary from pale brown with pink tones to dark brown or black. These are common benign skin lesions in older individuals. Mild itching of the lesion is common.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA\u003Cstrong\u003E melanoma \u003C/strong\u003Eis a tumour produced by the genetic malignant transformation of melanocytes. The exact cause of melanoma is not clear, but exposure to ultraviolet (UV) radiation and fair skin colour increases the risk of its development. The acronym \u0022ABCDE\u0022 is the hallmark used to remember the physical characteristics of melanoma. ABCDE stands for asymmetry, irregular border, color variations (especially red, white, and blue tones in a brown or black lesion), diameter greater than 6 mm, and elevated surface.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Elentigo\u003C/strong\u003E is a small, sharply circumscribed, pigmented macule surrounded by normal-appearing skin, unlike an ephelis, it does not fade in the winter months. Common forms of lentigo are due to exposure to ultraviolet radiations. It is a benign hyperplasia of melanocytes which is linear in its spread.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMelanocytic naevi\u003C/strong\u003E are benign neoplasms or hamartomas composed of melanocytes, commonly known as moles. Melanocytic naevi most commonly are tan to brown, tend to appear commonly during early childhood and during the first 30 years of life. They may be flat or protruding and can arise on any part of the body.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA\u003Cstrong\u003E pigmented basal cell carcinoma \u003C/strong\u003Eis\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003Enot translucent like a usual basal cell carcinoma and typically appears with brown or black shaded regions within the lesion. It sometimes resembles melanoma, but melanoma is commonly much darker throughout the entire lesion instead of in particular spots.\u0026nbsp;It presents with itching, burning and increased sensitivity to light. Erosion, ulceration, bleeding or crusting of the lesion might occur.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["A seborrhoeic keratosis is a common benign skin lesion in older individuals"],"references":["Yeatman JM, Kilkenny M, Marks R. The prevalence of seborrhoeic keratoses in an Australian population: does exposure to sunlight play a part in their frequency? Br J Dermatol. 1997 Sep. 137(3):411-4."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18018"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"698"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19155"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19155","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19155"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4b44ea95-292c-4fa4-b735-6b62078a383e.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4b44ea95-292c-4fa4-b735-6b62078a383e.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18018","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/18018"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-02-12T08:58:54+10:30","updatedAt":"2023-02-12T08:58:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"ty